#How to use the APIs

This file explains the procedure to test the Door Position API's used.
API Details:

 HwDoorPositionSensorInit( void ) => Initializes the ADC for Door Position.
 HwDoorPositionSensorReadStatus( HwDoorPosition_t *pStatus ) => Read the Door Position Status

Steps for Integration:

Include the API's related files inside the main.c File.

STEP 1 : Include the header files:
         Ensure that the header files are included in your main source file.
         
STEP 2: Initialize the Door Position:
        Call the HwDoorPositionSensorInit() function.

STEP 3: Read the Door Position Status:
        Call the HwDoorPositionSensorReadStatus() function and pass the arguments (HwDoorClampStatus_t *pStatus) for read status of door position.

Example:
Below is an example of how to test the APIs in the main function:

#include "HwDoorPositionSensor.h"
#include "main.h"

/*To test Door Clamp Status */

/*Initialize Door Position*/
  HwDoorPositionSensorInit();
  
/*Read Status Door Position Sensor */
HwDoorPosition_t *door_position

HwDoorPositionSensorReadStatus(door_position);

if(door_position == HW_DOORPOSITION_CLOSED)
   printf("Door Position Closed");
else if(door_position == HW_DOORPOSITION_HALFOPEN)
    printf("Door Position Half Open");
else if(door_position == HW_DOORPOSITION_FULLOPEN);    
    printf("Door Position Full Open");
    
    
    
    
   
